obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10253)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10253&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Offshore Areas Mineral`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 2002.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.15th January, 2010, vide notification no. S.O. 338(E), dated by 11th February, 2010, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10254)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of Union control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10254&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient in the`
  line `public interest that the Union should take under its control the regulation of mines and the development of`
  line `minerals in offshore areas to the extent herein after provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10255)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10255&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act shall apply to all minerals in the offshore areas including any mineral`
  line `prescribed by notification under clause (g) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Atomic Energy Act, 1962`
  line `(33 of 1962) except mineral oils and hydrocarbons related thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not`
  line `in derogation of, any other law for the time being in force in the offshore areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10256)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10256&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "administering authority" means an authority notified, in the Official Gazette, by the Central`
  line `Government for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "atomic minerals" means the minerals included in atomic minerals specified in Part B of the`
  line `First Schedule to the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Act, 1957 (67 of 1957)`
  line `^1[and the rules made thereunder;]`
  line
  line `(c) "Coast Guard" means the Coast Guard constituted under the Coast Guard Act, 1978`
  line `(30 of 1978);`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) "composite licence" means the exploration licence-cum-production lease, which is a two`
  line `stage operating right granted for the purpose of undertaking exploration operation followed by`
  line `production operation;`
  line
  line `(cb) "dispatch" means removal of minerals or mineral products from the area covered under the`
  line `production lease and includes the consumption of minerals and mineral products within such area;]`
  line
  line `(d) "exploration licence" means a licence granted ^2[for the purpose of undertaking exploration`
  line
  line operation];
  line
  line `(e) "exploration operation" means any operation undertaken for the purpose of exploring, locating`
  line `or proving the mineral deposits;`
  line
  line `^1[(ea) "Government company" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (45) of section 2 of`
  line `the Companies Act, 2013, (18 of 2013);]`
  line
  line `(f) "holder", in relation to any operating right, means the lessee, licensee or permittee, as the case`
  line `may be, in respect of such operating right;`
  line
  line `(g) "hydrocarbon" means very large group of chemical compounds composed of carbon and`
  line hydrogen;
  line
  line `(h) "Indian national" means a citizen of India and includes a firm or other association, if all the`
  line `members of the firm or, as the case may be, the members of the association, are citizens of India;`
  line
  line `(i) "lessee" means the person in whose name ^3[a production lease] is granted;`
  line
  line `(j) "licensee" means the person in whose name ^4[a composite licence, or an exploration licence, is`
  line grantedic;9563
  line
  line `(k) "mine" means any place in the offshore area wherein any exploration or production operation`
  line `is carried on, together with any vessel, erection, appliance, artificial island or platform and premises`
  line `in the offshore area used for the purposes of exploration, winning, treating or preparing minerals,`
  line `obtaining or extracting any mineral or metal by any mode or method, and includes any area covered`
  line `by ^5[a composite licence, or an exploration licence, or a production lease] where exploration or`
  line `production operation has been, or is being, or may be, carried on under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "mineral" includes all minerals except mineral oil and hydrocarbon resources relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(m) "mineral oil" includes natural gas and petroleum;`
  line
  line `(n) "offshore area" means the territorial waters, continental shelf, exclusive economic zone and`
  line `other maritime zones of India under the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic`
  line `Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(o) "operating right" means the right of holder of a reconnaissance permit, or ^6[a composite`
  line `licence, or an exploration licence, or a production lease;]`
  line
  line `(p) "permittee" means the person in whose name the reconnaissance permit is granted;`
  line
  line `(q) "pollution of offshore environment" means the introduction by any person, directly or`
  line `indirectly, of substances or energy into the offshore environment which results, or is likely to result,`
  line `in deleterious effect on living resources and marine life, hazards to human health, hindrance to marine`
  line `activities, including fishing and other legitimate uses of the offshore areas and impairment of quality`
  line `of sea water for use and reduction of amenities;`
  line
  line `(r) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^7[(ra) "production", with its grammatical variation and cognate expressions, means the winning`
  line `of mineral within the area covered under a production lease for the purpose of processing or`
  line dispatch;]
  line
  line `(s) "production operation" means any operation undertaken for the purpose of winning any`
  line `mineral from the offshore area and includes any operation directly or indirectly necessary there for or`
  line `incidental thereto;`
  line
  line `(t) "production lease" means a lease granted ^8[under section 8 or section 12 or section 13] which`
  line `confers an exclusive right for the purpose of undertaking production operation;`
  line
  line `(u) "reconnaissance operation" means any preliminary geo-scientific survey undertaken for the`
  line `purpose of searching or locating mineral deposits;`
  line
  line `(v) "reconnaissance permit" means a permit granted ^9*** for the purpose of undertaking`
  line `reconnaissance operation;`
  line
  line `^7[(va) "standard block" means a block of the offshore area of one minute latitude by one minute`
  line `longitude and includes the seabed and its subsoil and waters superjacent to the seabed within such`
  line block;]
  line
  line `(w) "vessel" includes any ship, ^10[barge, boat, container, sailing vessel or stationary vessel or any`
  line `other vessel of any description, submersible or otherwise and remotely operated or otherwise, used in`
  line `any operation or any activity pursuant thereto].`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "under section 12" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 2, for "the production lease" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the exploration licence is granted" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "an exploration licence or production lease" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "an exploration licence, or a production lease" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "under section 13" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `9. The words and figures "under section 11" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "boat, sailing vessel or any other vessel of any description" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10257)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Reconnaissance, exploration or production to be under permit, licence or lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10257&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `person shall undertake any reconnaissance operation, exploration operation or production operation in the`
  line `offshore areas, except under and in accordance with the prescribed terms and conditions of a`
  line `reconnaissance permit, ^1[a composite licence, or an exploration licence, or a production lease, granted].`
  line `under this Act and the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any reconnaissance operation or exploration`
  line `operation undertaken by the Geological Survey of India, ^2[Atomic Minerals Directorate for Exploration`
  line `and Research], the Chief Hydrographer to the Government of India of ^3[the National Hydrographic`
  line `Office[, the National Institute of Oceanography, the National Institute of Ocean Technology of`
  line `Department of Ocean Development of the Government of India, or ^4[any other agency including a private`
  line `entity, duly authorised in this behalf by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified therein.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Every permittee, licensee and lessee referred to in sub-section (1), and the Government`
  line `organisation, agency or private entity referred to in the proviso thereof, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) furnish to the administering authority and such other authority as may be prescribed, all`
  line `exploration and operational data, reports, samples and other information in respect of or collected`
  line `pursuant to an operation, in such manner and within such period, as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) all exploration and operational data, reports, samples and other information in respect of or`
  line `collected pursuant to an operation, shall be held by such permittee, licensee, lessee, Government`
  line `organisation, agency or private entity, as the case may be, in strict confidence and any dissemination,`
  line `pursuant to a sale or otherwise, of such data, reports or other information, or sharing of its samples, shall`
  line `be subject to such terms and conditions, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Central Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) authorise seaward artillery practice under the Seaward Artillery Practice Act, 1949`
  line `(8 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(b) provide for, by notification in the Official Gazette, special measures to ensure public safety`
  line `and interest, the defence of India and civil defence, conduct of the naval operations and exercises,`
  line `national security and other strategic considerations and the matters connected therewith during war`
  line `like conditions or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(4) No operating right shall be ^6[granted, extended or acquired otherwise than in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder and any reconnaissance permit, ^7[composite licence,`
  line `exploration licence or production lease, granted, extended or acquired] in contravention of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or any rules made thereunder, shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 3, for "exploration licence or production lease granted" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Atomic Minerals Directorate of Exploration and Research" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Naval Hydrographic Office of the Indian Navy" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "any other agency duly authorised in this behalf by the Central Government" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "granted or renewed" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "exploration licence or production lease granted, renewed or acquired" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10258)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Grant of operating right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10258&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall not grant an operating right to any`
  line `person unless such person--`
  line
  line `(a) is an Indian national, or a company as defined in ^1[clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)]; and`
  line
  line `(b) satisfies such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no exploration licence, or composite licence, or production lease shall be granted for`
  line `an area to any person other than the Government, a Government company or a corporation, in respect of`
  line `any minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule to the Mines and Minerals (Development and Regulation) Act, 1957 (67 of 1957), subject to such conditions and manner as may be prescribed, where`
  line `the grade of such mineral in such area is equal to or greater than such threshold value as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no production lease shall be granted in respect of any part of the offshore area,`
  line `unless the existence of mineral resources in such offshore area has been adequately established in`
  line `accordance with such parameters as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 4, for "section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10259)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Termination of operating right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10259&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government, after consultation with the`
  line `administering authority, is of the opinion ^1[that it is expedient in public interest, strategic interest of the`
  line `country, in the interest of] development and regulation of offshore mineral resources, preservation of`
  line `natural environment and prevention of pollution, avoidance of danger to public health or communication,`
  line `ensuring safety of any offshore structure or conservation of mineral resources ^2[or for any other reason],`
  line `the Central Government may prematurely terminate any operating right in respect of any mineral in any`
  line `offshore area or part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) No order for premature termination of operating right under sub-section (1) shall be made except`
  line `after giving the holder of operating right a reasonable ^3[opportunity of being heard, except in cases where`
  line `premature termination is being done on the grounds of strategic interest of the country].`
  line
  line `(3) Where the holder of any operating right fails to commence operation within the period specified in`
  line `section 14 or discontinues the operation for a period of two years, the operating right shall lapse from the`
  line `date of execution of the lease or, as the case may be, discontinuance of the operation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the administering authority, on an application made by the holder of operating right and`
  line `after being satisfied that such non-commencement of operation or discontinuation thereof, is due to the`
  line `reasons beyond the control of the holder of operating right, may ^4[extend the period specified in`
  line `section 14 by a further period not exceeding one year and such extension shall not be granted for more`
  line `than once during the entire period of operating right:]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided further that where the holder of operating right--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to undertake operation; or`
  line
  line `(b) having commenced the operation, discontinues such operation,`
  line
  line `before the end of the extended period, such operating right shall also lapse from the date of execution of`
  line `the lease or, as the case may be, discontinuance of the operation.]`
  line
  line `^5[(4) Where the holder of a production lease fails to undertake production and dispatch for a period of`
  line `four years after the date of execution of the lease, or having commenced production and dispatch,`
  line `discontinues the same for a period of two years, then such lease shall lapse on the expiry of the period of`
  line `four years from the date of its execution or, as the case may be, two years from date of discontinuance of`
  line `the production and dispatch:`
  line
  line `Provided that the administering authority may, on an application made by the lessee, and after being`
  line `satisfied that such non-commencement of production, or dispatch, or discontinuation thereof, was due to`
  line `the reasons beyond the control of the lessee, may extend such period by a further period not exceeding`
  line `one year, but such extension shall not be granted for more than once during the entire period of lease:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the lessee,--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to undertake production or dispatch; or`
  line
  line `(b) having commenced the production and dispatch, discontinues the same,`
  line
  line `before the end of the extended period, such lease shall lapse from the date of its execution or, as the case`
  line `may be, discontinuance of production or dispatch.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 5, for "that it is expedient in the interest of" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "opportunity of being heard" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "condone such non-commencement or discontinuation." (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 5, ibid., (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10260)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Reservation of areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 6 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10260&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, reserve any offshore area not already held under any operating right, for the purposes of the Central Government and, where it proposes to do so, it shall, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify the boundaries of such area and the mineral or minerals in respect of which such area shall be`
  line reserved.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `dereserve, any area reserved under sub-section (1), in the interest of development and regulation of the`
  line `offshore mineral.`
  line
  line `^1](3) Where the Central Government reserves any offshore area under sub-section (1), the`
  line `administering authority may, subject to such terms and conditions as may be prescribed, grant a`
  line `composite licence, or a production lease, in such area or any part thereof to the Government, or a`
  line `Government company, or a corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) A composite licence or a production lease granted to the Government, or a Government company,`
  line `or a corporation under sub-section (3) shall be subject to the same terms and conditions applicable to a`
  line `licensee or a lessee, as the case may be, except the procedure specified for grant of a composite licence`
  line `under section 12 or a production lease under section 13.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a Government company, or corporation is desirous of carrying out the exploration`
  line `operation or production operation in a joint venture with other persons, the joint venture partner shall be`
  line `selected through a competitive process, and such Government company or corporation shall hold more`
  line `than seventy-four per cent. of the paid up share capital in such joint venture.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10261)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of close areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10261&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in the public interest, by order in`
  line `writing and communicated to the permittee, licensee or lessee, as the case may be, close any area either in`
  line `part or whole, covered under any operating right, for`
  line `^1[such period as may be specified in the order, for]`
  line `the preservation of natural environment and prevention of pollution, or to avoid danger to public health,`
  line `or communication, or to ensure safety of any offshore structure or platform, or for the conservation of`
  line `^2[offshore mineral, or for regulation of offshore areas, or for national security] or for any other strategic`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(2) Any area, either in part or whole closed under sub-section (1) and included in any operating right,`
  line `shall, from the date of such order, be deemed to be excluded for the purposes of the operating right ^1[for`
  line `such period as may be specified in the order and the holder of the operating right shall not undertake any`
  line `operation in the area covered under such order ^3[during the period of closure specified therein].`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 7, (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "offshore mineral, or for national security" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "from the date specified therein" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10262)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Availability of areas for grant of permit, licence or lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10262&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[Within six months] from the date`
  line `of commencement of this Act, and subsequently at such times as may be considered necessary in this`
  line `behalf by the administering authority, it shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare the parts of`
  line `the offshore areas which shall be available for grant of ^2[reconnaissance permit, or exploration licence, or`
  line `composite licence, or production lease].`
  line
  line `^3[* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 8, for "(1) Within six months" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "reconnaissance permit, exploration licence or production lease" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) and (3) omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10263)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10263&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The administering authority may grant a non-exclusive`
  line `reconnaissance permit to any person eligible under section 6 for grant of operating right.`
  line
  line `(2) The period for which a reconnaissance permit may be granted under sub-section (1) shall be for a`
  line `period specified in such permit which shall not exceed two years.`
  line
  line `(3) A reconnaissance permit granted under sub-section (1) may be renewed for a period not exceeding`
  line `two years if, after a review of the progress made during the period of such grant, the administering`
  line `authority is satisfied that a further period is necessary to complete the reconnaissance operation.`
  line
  line `(4) The area that may be granted under one reconnaissance permit shall not exceed a block of two`
  line `degree latitude by two degree longitude.`
  line
  line `(5) The administering authority may grant reconnaissance permits to more than one person in respect`
  line `of the same area for the same mineral deposits in the interest of offshore mineral development.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (10264)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Grant of composite licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 10, for section 12 and 13 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10264&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Grant of composite licence.--(1) The administering authority may, in respect of an offshore`
  line `area where the existence of mineral resources has not been adequately established for grant of a`
  line `production lease as required by the second proviso to section 6, after inviting applications in this behalf,`
  line `select any person for grant of a composite licence, who--`
  line
  line `(a) fulfils the eligibility conditions as specified in this Act and such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) is selected through auction by method of competitive bidding, including e-auction, conducted`
  line `on the basis of such terms and conditions, manner and bidding parameters, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall grant the composite licence to the person selected in accordance`
  line `with the procedure laid down in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The licensee shall complete the exploration operations satisfactorily, as specified in the notice`
  line `inviting applications, within a period of three years from the date of grant of the composite licence:`
  line `Provided that the administering authority may, on an application made by the licensee three months`
  line `before the lapse of the said period, for reasons to be recorded in writing and subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed, grant an extension for a period of two years to the licensee for satisfactory completion`
  line `of the exploration operations:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no further extension shall be granted upon expiry of the extended period, if any,`
  line `granted under the first proviso.`
  line
  line `(4) The area granted under a composite licence shall comprise of contiguous standard blocks, which`
  line `in aggregate do not exceed an area of thirty minutes latitude by thirty minutes longitude.`
  line
  line `(5) Every licensee shall, on being granted a composite licence, commence and carry out exploration`
  line `operation subject to such terms, milestones and relinquishment requirements, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) A licensee, who has adequately established the existence of mineral resources in an offshore area`
  line `held under the composite licence, or part thereof, as required by the second proviso to section 6, shall,`
  line `within the period specified or extended under sub-section (3), subject to such terms and conditions, and`
  line `on making an application to the administering authority in such form, as may be prescribed, be granted`
  line `one or more production leases:`
  line
  line `Provided that such licensee--`
  line
  line `(a) is not in breach of the terms and conditions of his composite licence;`
  line
  line `(b) continues to be eligible for grant of a production lease in accordance with section 6; and`
  line
  line `(c) has applied for grant of production lease within six months of completion of his exploration`
  line `operations:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the total area of such production lease or production leases, granted in`
  line `pursuance of a single composite licence, shall not exceed fifteen minutes latitude by fifteen minutes`
  line longitude.
  line
  line `(7) The administering authority shall, on receipt of an application under sub-section (6), and on being`
  line `satisfied that the licensee meets the requirements under the provisions of this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, recommend to the Central Government for grant of production lease to such licensee.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government shall, on receipt of a recommendation under sub-section (7) from the`
  line `administering authority, grant production lease to the licensee in accordance with such procedure as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Every production lease granted in pursuance of a composite licence shall be for a period of fifty`
  line years.
  line
  line `(10) All rights and interests held under a composite licence in the parts of an offshore area, in respect`
  line `of which no production lease is granted, shall cease to exist upon expiry of the composite licence.`
  line
  line `(11) The provisions of this section shall not apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the areas covered under section 8; and`
  line
  line `(b) the minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule to the Mines and Minerals (Development`
  line `and Regulation) Act, 1957, (67 of 1957) where the grade of atomic mineral is equal to or greater than`
  line `such threshold value, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (10265)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Grant of production lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 10, for section 12 and 13 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10265&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Grant of production lease.-- (1) The administering authority may, in respect of an offshore area`
  line `where the existence of mineral resources has been adequately established for grant of production lease as`
  line `required by the second proviso to section 6, after inviting applications in this behalf, select any person for`
  line `grant of a production lease, who--`
  line
  line `(a) fulfils the eligibility conditions as specified in this Act and such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) is selected through auction by method of competitive bidding, including e-auction, conducted`
  line `on the basis of such terms and conditions, manner and bidding parameters, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall grant the production lease to the applicant selected in accordance`
  line `with the procedure laid down under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Every production lease under this section shall be granted for a period of fifty years.`
  line
  line `(4) The area under a production lease shall comprise of contiguous standard blocks and shall not`
  line `exceed an area of fifteen minutes latitude by fifteen minutes longitude.`
  line
  line `(5) Upon grant of a production lease, the lessee shall commence and carry out production operation in`
  line `such manner and subject to such terms and conditions, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall not apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the areas covered under section 8; and`
  line
  line `(b) the minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule to the Mines and Minerals (Development`
  line `and Regulation) Act, 1957 (67 of 1957), where the grade of atomic mineral is equal to or greater than`
  line `such threshold value, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line specify.]
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (76986)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 14
  title `Maximum area for which operating rights may be granted`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 11 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76986&sectionno=13A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Maximum area for which operating rights may be granted.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 12 or section 13, no person shall acquire in respect of any mineral or a group of`
  line `associated minerals, as may be prescribed, one or more exploration licence, composite licence and`
  line `production lease, all taken together and covering a total area of more than forty-five minutes latitude by`
  line `forty-five minutes longitude:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government is of the opinion that in the interest of the development of`
  line `any mineral or industry, it is necessary so to do, it may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, increase`
  line `or decrease the said area limit in respect of any mineral or any specified category of deposits of such`
  line `mineral or such group of associated minerals.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a person acquiring by, or in the name of, another person an`
  line `operating right which is intended for himself, shall be deemed to be acquiring it himself.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of determining the total area referred to in sub-section (1), the area held under an`
  line `operating right by a person as a member of a co-operative society, or a company, or a corporation, or a`
  line `Hindu undivided family, or a partner of a firm, shall be deducted from the area referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) so that the sum total of the area held by such person, under an operating right, whether as`
  line `such member or partner, or individually, may not, in any case, exceed the total area specified in`
  line `sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (76987)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 15
  title `Transfer of composite licence or production lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 11 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76987&sectionno=13B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[13B. Transfer of composite licence or production lease.-- (1) A composite licence or a production`
  line `lease granted under section 8, or through competitive bidding under section 12 or section 13, may be`
  line `transferred by the relevant licensee or lessee, as the case may be, in such manner and subject to such`
  line `conditions, as may be prescribed, to any person eligible for grant of such licence or lease, under the`
  line `provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such transfer of a composite licence or a production lease shall be made in`
  line `contravention of any conditions, subject to which such licence or lease was granted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, it is clarified that transfer may include one or`
  line `more production leases, granted pursuant to one composite licence.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act, the rules made thereunder and the terms and conditions of a composite`
  line `licence or a production lease, shall be binding upon the person to whom such licence or lease, as the case`
  line `may be, is transferred under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_c:
  sectionId (76988)
  sectionNo 13C
  orderNo 16
  title `Certain applications and exploration licence to become ineligible.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 11 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76988&sectionno=13C&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[13C. Certain applications and exploration licence to become ineligible.--(1) On and from the`
  line `date of commencement of the Offshore Areas Mineral (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2023, auction being the sole method of selection for grant of composite licence or production lease under`
  line `sections 12 and 13,--`
  line
  line `(a) all applications received prior to the said date of commencement for grant of composite`
  line `licence or production lease shall become ineligible;`
  line
  line `(b) any exploration licence granted prior to the said date of commencement shall become`
  line `ineligible for grant of production lease over the offshore area covered by such exploration licence.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall be applicable notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, or any order or direction to the contrary, passed by any court or authority, prior to the`
  line `commencement of the Offshore Areas Mineral (Development and Regulation) Amendment Act, 2023.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (10266)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Period of commencement of operating rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 12, (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10266&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `A holder of operating right shall commence`
  line `operation within the period specified below after the grant of the operating right and shall thereafter`
  line `conduct such operation in proper, skilful and workman-like manner, as follows:--`
  line
  line `^table(a) reconnaissance permitsix months;`
  line `^1[(aa) composite licence one year;]`
  line `(b) exploration licenceone year; and`
  line `(c) production leasetwo years.`
  line ^/table
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (10267)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Central Government to authorise survey, research and scientific investigations in areas covered under operating rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10267&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person or agency authorised by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, by the Central Government in this behalf, may conduct survey, research, diving operations and`
  line `scientific investigations in the offshore areas, including any area covered under operating rights and the`
  line `permittee, licensee or lessee, as the case may be, shall permit such person or agency to undertake the said`
  line `investigations in their respective areas and to render such assistance as may be necessary for conduct of`
  line `the investigations.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (10268)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title Royalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 13, for "consumed by him from the area covered under the production" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10268&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A lessee shall pay royalty to the Central Government in respect of any mineral`
  line `removed or ^1[consumed from the area covered under his production] lease, at the rate for the time being`
  line `specified in the First Schedule in respect of that mineral.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the First Schedule so`
  line `as to enhance or reduce the rate at which royalty shall be payable in respect of any mineral with effect`
  line `from such date as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not enhance the rate of royalty in respect of any mineral`
  line `more than once during any period of three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (76989)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 20
  title `Establishment of Offshore Areas Mineral Trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 14, (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76989&sectionno=16A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Establishment of Offshore Areas Mineral Trust.--(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, establish a Trust, as a non-profit autonomous body, to be called the`
  line `Offshore Areas Mineral Trust.`
  line
  line `(2) The object of the Offshore Areas Mineral Trust shall be to use the funds accrued to it for the`
  line `following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) research, administration, studies and related expenditure with respect to offshore areas and`
  line `mitigation of any adverse impact that may be caused to the ecology in the offshore area, due to`
  line `operations undertaken; or`
  line
  line `(b) providing relief upon the occurrence of any disaster in the offshore area; or`
  line
  line `(c) the purposes of exploration in the offshore area; or`
  line
  line `(d) for the interest and benefit of persons affected by exploration or production operations`
  line `undertaken; or`
  line
  line `(e) such other purposes, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The composition and functions of the Offshore Areas Mineral Trust shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) The funds accrued to the Offshore Areas Mineral Trust shall be non-lapsable under the public`
  line `account of India and be administered in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) A lessee shall pay, in addition to the royalty, to the Offshore Areas Mineral Trust, an amount`
  line `which is equivalent to such percentage of the royalty paid in terms of the First Schedule, not exceeding`
  line `one-third of such royalty, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The entities specified and notified under sub-section (1) of section 5 shall be eligible for funding`
  line `under the Offshore Areas Mineral Trust, subject to such conditions as may be specified by the Central`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (10269)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Fixed rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 15, for "consumed by him from the area" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10269&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A lessee shall pay to the Central Government, every year, fixed rent in respect`
  line `of the area covered under the production lease, at the rate for the time being specified in the Second`
  line `Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the lessee becomes liable under section 16 to pay royalty for any mineral`
  line `removed or ^1[consumed from the area] covered under such lease, he shall be liable to pay either such`
  line `royalty or the fixed rent in respect of that area, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the Second Schedule`
  line `so as to enhance or reduce the rate at which fixed rent shall be payable in respect of any area covered`
  line `under a production lease and such enhancement or reduction shall take effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not enhance the rate of the fixed rent more than once`
  line `during any period of three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (10270)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Contribution towards International Seabed Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 16, for section 18 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10270&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[Every lessee shall, in addition to`
  line `other payments required under this Act, pay to the Central Government in advance, the amount to be paid`
  line `to the International Seabed Authority in respect of the offshore area granted under his production lease`
  line `falling in such part of the continental shelf extending beyond two hundred nautical miles, from the`
  line `baseline from which the breadth of the territorial sea is measured, towards fulfilment of the obligation of`
  line `the Government of India under Article 82 of the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea, 1982.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (10271)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Safety of persons and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10271&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The permittee, licensee, lessee or any other person undertaking the reconnaissance operation or exploration operation or production operation under sub-section (1) of section 5 or any agency undertaking the reconnaissance operation or exploration operation under the proviso to sub-section (1) of the said section shall be responsible to ensure that the concerned operation is conducted with due regard to the safety and health of persons including divers and safety and security of property engaged in the operation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare safety zones in respect of offshore activities as may be necessary and prescribe the norms for regulating the safety and health of persons and safety of property engaged in operations authorised under this Act, the implementation thereof and matters connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of any contravention of provisions of sub-section (1) or the norms prescribed under sub-section (2) by the permittee, licensee, lessee or any other person undertaking the reconnaissance operation or exploration operation or production operation under sub-section (1) of section 5, or any other agency undertaking the reconnaissance operation or exploration operation under the proviso to sub-section (1) of the said section, shall also be deemed to be responsible for such contravention unless he or it proves that he or it, as the case may be, had taken all reasonable precautions within his or its means for enforcing those provisions, to prevent such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (76990)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 24
  title `Duty of Central Government on mineral conservation and development`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 17, (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76990&sectionno=19A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Duty of Central Government on mineral conservation and development.--The Central`
  line `Government shall take necessary steps, as may be prescribed, for the conservation and systematic`
  line `development of minerals in the offshore areas and for the protection of environment by preventing or`
  line `controlling any pollution which may be caused by exploration or production operations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (10272)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Prevention and control of pollution and protection of marine environment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10272&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every holder of the operating rights shall carry out the operations authorised under this Act subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder and any other law and the rules made thereunder, for the time being in force for the prevention and control of pollution and protection of marine environment.`
  line
  line `(2) Every holder of an operating right shall be liable for any pollution of, or damage to, the marine environment resulting from his activities relating to his operating right in the offshore areas and shall pay such compensation, as may be determined by the administering authority keeping in view the extent of pollution or damage, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may prescribe measures to be taken for prevention and control of pollution and protection of marine environment due to activities in the offshore areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (10273)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of Central Government and administering authority to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10273&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The permittee, licensee or lessee shall comply with such directions as the Central Government or the administering authority may issue, from time to time, for the conservation and systematic development of offshore minerals, prevention of pollution, protection of marine environment, prevention of coastal erosion or prevention of danger to life or property including the marine life.`
  line
  line `(2) The permittee, licensee or lessee shall comply with such directions as may be issued from time to time by the competent authority or Coast Guard regarding national security, safety and national integrity.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"competent authority" means the competent authority appointed for the purposes of sub-section (2) by the Central Government in the Ministry dealing with defence of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (10274)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of entry, inspection, search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10274&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of ascertaining the position of the working, actual or prospective, of any mine or abandoned mine, or for any other purpose connected with this Act or the rules made thereunder, any officer authorised, by the Central Government in this behalf, by general or special order, may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter and inspect, at all reasonable times, any mine;`
  line
  line `(b) weigh, draw samples or take measurements of the stocks of minerals recovered from any mine;`
  line
  line `(c) survey and take samples and measurements in any such mine;`
  line
  line `(d) examine any document, book, register or record in the possession or power of any person having the control of, or connected with, any mine and place marks of identification thereon and take extracts from, or make copies of, such document, book, register or record;`
  line
  line `(e) order the production of any such document, book, register and record, by the person referred to in clause (d); and`
  line
  line `(f) examine any person having the control of, or connected with, any mine.`
  line
  line `(2) Any authorised officer may, for the purpose of ascertaining whether or not the requirements of this Act or any rule made thereunder have been complied with, either with, or where it is not possible to obtain warrant conveniently, then, without, a warrant,--`
  line
  line `(a) search any mine;`
  line
  line `(b) stop or board and search any vessel which is engaged or which is likely to be engaged in any activity regulated under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) require the person for the time being having command or charge of mine or such vessel to produce any licence, permit, log book or other document relating, to the vessel or mine and examine or take copies of such licence, permit, log book or other document, as the case may be, for ascertaining the requirements of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the authorised officer has reason to believe that any vessel or mine has been, or is being, or is about to be, used or employed, as the case may be, in violation of any provision of this Act or rule made thereunder, he may, with, or where it is not possible to obtain warrant conveniently, then, without, a warrant,--`
  line
  line `(a) seize and detain such vessel or mine, including any gear, equipment, stores or cargo found on board such vessel or belonging to the vessel and seize any mineral found on board the vessel;`
  line
  line `(b) seize any evidence relating to violation of any provision of this Act or rule made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) require the person for the time being having command or charge of the vessel, platform or erection of the mine so seized or detained to bring such vessel, platform or erection to any specified port;`
  line
  line `(d) arrest any person whom such officer has reason to believe, has committed such violation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authorised officer, after arresting such person and before producing him before the competent court, shall inform the administering authority regarding the arrest and grounds of arrest communicated to the person so arrested.`
  line
  line `(4) In taking any action under sub-section (3), the authorised officer may use such force as may be reasonably necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any vessel or other things are seized or detained, under sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(a) the vessel or other things so seized or detained shall, as soon as possible, be produced before the court competent to try an offence under this Act and the court shall make such order as it may deem fit for the retention or custody of such vessel or things with the Central Government or any other authority pending the completion of any proceedings for the prosecution of any offence relating to such vessel or things, as the case may be, under this Act or rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, on an application made by the owner or the person for the time being having command or charge of the vessel or mine, order the release of the vessel or other things so seized or detained, to the owner or the person for the tie being having command or charge of the vessel or mine, furnishing security in the form of cash or a bank guarantee for an amount which is not less than fifty per cent. of the value of the vessel or things so seized or detained;`
  line
  line `(b) the administering authority shall be informed by the authorised officer of such seizure and the details thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) Where, in pursuance of the commission of any offence under this Act, any vessel is pursued beyond the limits of the offshore area, the powers conferred on an authorised officer by this section may be exercised beyond such limits in the circumstances and to the extent recognised by international law and State practice.`
  line
  line `(7) Every person to whom an order or warrant is issued or given by virtue of the powers conferred by this section shall be legally bound to comply with such order or warrant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "authorised officer" means an officer of the Central Government notified as such in the Official Gazette, by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) "warrant" means a warrant issued by the Judicial Magistrate or the Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may be, within whose jurisdiction the place, where the warrant is to be executed, is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (10275)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10275&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[(a) whoever undertakes any reconnaissance operation, or exploration operation,`
  line `or production operation in an offshore area without a reconnaissance permit, or a composite licence, or an`
  line `exploration licence, or a production lease, as the case may be, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years, or with fine of five lakh rupees, which may extend to ten lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) any permittee or licensee or lessee, who fails to furnish the required data, or information, or`
  line `document under sub-section (2) of section 5 in the manner provided therein, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine of five lakh rupees, which may extend to ten`
  line `lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b), the amount of fine provided shall be in respect`
  line `of each standard block of such part of the offshore area where such reconnaissance operation, or`
  line `exploration operation, or production operation is undertaken.]`
  line
  line `(c) Any vessel, together with its gear, boats, stores and cargo, used or employed in violation of`
  line `section 5, along with any mineral recovered or processed in violation of that section, if any, shall be`
  line confiscated.
  line
  line `(d) Whoever ships, transports, offers for sale, sells, purchases, imports, exports, or has custody,`
  line `control or possession of, any mineral recovered, processed or retained in violation of this Act or any rule`
  line `made thereunder shall be ^2[punishable] with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to three years, or ^3[with fine of twenty-five lakh rupees, which may extend to fifty lakh`
  line `rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) intentionally obstructs any authorised officer referred to in section 22 in the exercise of any`
  line `powers conferred under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to afford reasonable facilities to the authorised officer referred to in section 22 or his`
  line `assistant to board the vessel or enter the mine or to provide for adequate security to such officer or`
  line `assistant at the time of entry into the vessel or mine or when they are on board such vessel or mine; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails to stop the vessel or mine or to produce the licence, permit, log book or any other`
  line `document, as the case may be, on board such vessel, or mine, when required to do so by the`
  line `authorised officer referred to in section 22; or`
  line
  line `(d) interferes with, delays, or prevents, by any means, the lawful apprehension of any person`
  line `under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be ^4[punishable with imprisonment which may extend to five years, or with fine of two lakh rupees,`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `^5[(2A) Whoever, having been convicted of an offence under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), is`
  line `again convicted of an offence under that sub-section, shall, in addition to the punishment provided`
  line `therefor, be punishable with additional fine which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during`
  line `which he continues to commit that offence.]`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes any other provision of this Act ^6***, other than those specified in subsections (1) and (2) shall be ^7[punishable] with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years,`
  line `or ^8[with fine of fifty lakh rupees, which may extend to one crore rupees], or with both, and in the case of`
  line `continuing contravention, with an additional fine which may extend to five lakh rupees for every day`
  line `during which such contravention continues.`
  line
  line `^5[(4) Any rule made under any provision of this Act may provide that any contravention thereof shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years or with fine of fifty lakh`
  line `rupees, which may extend to one crore rupees, or with both, and in the case of a continuing contravention,`
  line `with additional fine which may extend to five lakh rupees for every day during which such contravention`
  line `continues after conviction for the first such contravention.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 18, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "punished" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "with fine which may extend to fifty lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to fifty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `6. The words "or the rules made thereunder" omitted by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "punished" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for "with fine which may extend to one crore rupees " (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (10276)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10276&sectionno=24&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge and that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act, has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary, or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means anybody corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (10277)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10277&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in other law for the time being in force, any person committing an offence under this Act or any rule made thereunder or under any of the enactment extended under this Act or under the rules made the reunder shall be tried for the offence in such place as the Central Government may, by general or special order published in the Official Gazette, direct in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (10278)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 31
  title `Previous sanction of Central Government for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10278&sectionno=26&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence`
  line `committed under t`
  line `his Act shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government`
  line `or such officer or authorit`
  line `y as may be authorised by the Ce`
  line `ntral Government, by order in writing in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (10279)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 32
  title `Offences triable by Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10279&sectionno=27&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences under this Act shall be triable by the Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (10280)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 33
  title `Civil liability and adjudication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 19, for "one lakh rupees and which may extend to ten lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10280&sectionno=28&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `A person to whom a permit, licence or lease is granted under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes the general terms and conditions imposed by the rules made under this Act shall be liable to pay to the Central Government an amount which shall not be less than five lakh rupees and which may extend to one crore rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes any particular terms and conditions applicable only in case of such permittee,`
  line `licensee or lessee as the case may be, shall also be liable, apart from the liability under clause (a), to`
  line `pay additional amount to the Central Government which shall not be less than ^1[five lakh rupees and`
  line `which may extend to fifty lakh rupees].`
  line
  line `(2) No court or other authority except the authorised officer designated by the Central Government for this purpose, shall have jurisdiction to hear and decide the cases relating to clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) An officer of the Central Government who has been authorised by that Government to file an application before the authorised officer designated under sub-section (2), shall file an application against licensee, lessee or permittee, as the case may be, indicating the civil wrong committed by him under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) When an application is filed under sub-section (3), before an authorised officer designated under sub-section (2), he shall serve notice along with the copy of such application to the person, against whom the application is made, to provide him an opportunity to file reply to the application in the prescribed manner and the authorised officer shall dispose of the case after considering the evidence produced either in support or in opposition to the application and after providing the opportunity of hearing.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, the authorised officer designated under sub-section (2), shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (10281)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 34
  title `Extension of enactments to offshore areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10281&sectionno=29&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) extend with such restrictions and modifications as it thinks fit, any enactment for the time being in force in India or any part thereof to the offshore area or any part thereof; and`
  line
  line `(b) make such provisions as it may consider necessary for facilitating the enforcement of such enactment,`
  line
  line `and any enactment so extended shall have effect as if the offshore area or the part thereof, as the case may be, is a part of the territory of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (10282)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 35
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10282&sectionno=30&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any offence punishable under this Act may, either before or after the institution of the prosecution, be compounded by the administering authority or any other officer authorised by the Central Government with respect to that offence, on payment for credit to that Government of such sum as that administering authority or officer, as the case may be, may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sum shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine which may be imposed under this Act for the offence so compounded.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence is compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further proceeding, as the case may be, shall be taken against the offender in respect of the offence so compounded and the offender, if in custody, shall be released forthwith.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (10283)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 36
  title `Recovery of certain sums as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10283&sectionno=31&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any licence fee, royalty, fixed rent or other sum due to the Central Government under this Act or rules made thereunder or under the terms and`
  line `conditions of a reconnaissance permit, exploration licence or production lease may, on a certificate issued`
  line `by the administering authority, be recovered in the same manner as if it were an arrear of land revenue`
  line `and every such sum together with the interest due thereon, shall`
  line `be the first charge on the assets of the permittee, licensee or lessee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (10284)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 37
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10284&sectionno=32&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act or any rule`
  line `made thereunder may, in relation to such`
  line `matter and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercisable also`
  line `by such officer or authority subordinate to that Government as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (10285)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 38
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10285&sectionno=33&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or`
  line `any rule made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (10286)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 39
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10286&sectionno=34&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), any person aggrieved by an order made by the administering authority or any officer under this Act or the rules made thereunder may prefer an appeal against such order to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such appeal shall be preferred within prescribed period from the date on which the impugned order was made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within such prescribed period, permit the appellant to prefer the appeal within a further period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of any such appeal, the Central Government shall, after giving the parties to the appeal a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after making such inquiry as it deems proper, make such order, as it may think fit, confirming, modifying or reversing the order appealed against, or may send back the case with such direction as it may think fit for a fresh order after taking additional evidence, if necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (76991)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of revision by Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 20 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76991&sectionno=34A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[34A. Power of revision by Central Government.--The Central Government may, of its own`
  line `motion and for reasons to be recorded in writing, and in accordance with such terms as may be prescribed,`
  line `revise any order made by the administering authority or any officer under this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder.]
obj_root_law_sections_34_b:
  sectionId (76992)
  sectionNo 34B
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 20 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76992&sectionno=34B&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_34_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[34B. Power of Central Government to issue directions.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may give such directions to the administering authority, as it may deem`
  line `necessary, in public interest, strategic interest of the country, conservation and development of mineral, or`
  line `to carry out the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_c:
  sectionId (76993)
  sectionNo 34C
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Central Government to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 20 (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=76993&sectionno=34C&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_34_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[34C. Power of Central Government to call for information.--The Central Government may, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, require--`
  line
  line `(a) the administering authority; or`
  line `(b) a permittee or a licensee or a lessee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any person whom it has reason to believe to be connected with any activity in respect of`
  line `minerals in the offshore area,`
  line
  line `to furnish such information as it may deem necessary for, or relevant to, any enquiry or proceeding, under`
  line `this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (10287)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10287&sectionno=35&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of a reconnaissance permit, exploration licence or production lease`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) such other authority to whom, all exploration and operational data, reports, samples and`
  line `other information in respect of or collected pursuant to an operation, is to be furnished by the lessee,`
  line `licensee or permittee the manner and the period within which, they are to be furnished, under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(ab) the terms and conditions subject to which the data, reports, samples or information is to be`
  line `disseminated pursuant to a sale or otherwise under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line `(b) conditions for grant of operating right under clause (b) of section 6;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) the conditions and manner for regulating the grant of mineral concessions in respect of`
  line `minerals specified in Part B of the First Schedule to the Mines and Minerals (Development and`
  line `Regulation) Act, 1957 (67 of 1957), under the first proviso to section 6;`
  line
  line `(ca) the parameters for adequately establishing existence of mineral resources under the second`
  line `proviso to section 6;]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^1[(ja) the terms and conditions for grant of a composite licence or a production lease to a`
  line `Government company or corporation under section 8;`
  line
  line `(jb) the eligibility conditions to be fulfilled, the terms and conditions for conducting competitive`
  line `bidding, the manner and bidding parameters for grant of a composite licence under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(jc) the conditions subject to which extension is to be granted to the licensee for completion of the`
  line `exploration operations under the first proviso to sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(jd) terms, milestone and relinquishment requirements for commencing and carrying out`
  line `exploration operation under sub-section (5) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(je) the form of application to be made to the administering authority for grant of production lease`
  line `under sub-section (6) and the procedure therefor under sub-section (8) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(jf) eligibility conditions to be fulfilled, the terms and conditions for conducting competitive`
  line `bidding, the manner and bidding parameters for grant of a production lease under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(jg) the terms and conditions subject to which the production operations shall be commenced and`
  line `carried out under sub-section (5) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(jh) the group of associated minerals to be specified under sub-section (1) of section 13A;`
  line
  line `(ji) the manner and the conditions for transfer of a composite licence or a production lease under`
  line `section 13B;`
  line
  line `(jj) such other purposes for which the funds accrued to the Offshore Area Mineral Trust shall be`
  line `used under sub-section (2) of section 16A;`
  line
  line `(jk) the composition and functions of the Offshore Area Mineral Trust under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 16A;`
  line
  line `(jl) the manner of administration of funds accrued to the Offshore Area Mineral Trust under subsection (4) of section 16A;`
  line
  line `(jm) the manner of payment of amounts to the Offshore Area Mineral Trust under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 16A;]`
  line
  line `(k) norms for regulating the safety and health of persons and safety of property engaged in`
  line `operations authorised under this Act, the implementation thereof and matters connected therewith`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line
  line `^4[(ka) the steps necessary to be taken for conservation and systematic development of minerals in`
  line `the offshore areas and for the protection of environment by preventing or controlling any pollution`
  line `which may be caused by exploration or production operations under section 19A;]`
  line
  line `(l) the measures to be taken for prevention and control of pollution and protection of marine`
  line `environment due to activities in the offshore areas under sub-section (3) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of filing application under sub-section (3) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of filing reply under sub-section (4) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter under clause (f) of sub-section (5) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(p) the period within which appeal shall be preferred under, and the further period which may be`
  line `permitted under the proviso to, sub-section (2) of section 34;`
  line
  line `^4[(pa) the measures to be taken for preventing illegal mining, transportation, and storage of`
  line `minerals and for the purposes connected therewith;]`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 2023, s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Clauses (d) to (j) omitted by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 21, ibid (w.e.f. 17-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (10288)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 44
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10288&sectionno=36&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act or`
  line `any rule made thereunder, the Central Government may, if it is of the opinion that in the interests of the offshore mineral development, it is necessary so`
  line `to do, by order and for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `authorise in any specific case the grant, renewal or transfer of any operating right to any person on such terms and conditions as it may specify in this behalf in such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (10289)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 45
  title `Persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10289&sectionno=37&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The administering authority or any other officer shall be`
  line `deemed, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (10290)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 46
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201&sectionId=10290&sectionno=38&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_15_16_000010_200317_1517807327201
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `or of any of the enactments extended under section 29, the Central Gover`
  line `nment may, by order published`
  line `in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or, as the`
  line `case may be, of such enactment, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line Provided
  line `that no order shall be made under this section,`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any difficulty arising in giving effect to any provision of this Act, after the`
  line `expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of such provision;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any difficulty arising in`
  line `giving effect to the provisions of any enactment`
  line `extended under section 29, after the expiry of three years from the extensi`
  line `on of such enactment.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
